[[Sodium bicarbonate]] may be used to neutralise liquid spills of phosgene. Gaseous spills may be mitigated with [[ammonia]].&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web |publisher= [[International Programme on Chemical Safety]] |title= Phosgene: Health and Safety Guide |year= 1998 |url= http://www.inchem.org/documents/hsg/hsg/hsg106.htm}}&lt;/ref&gt;

===Accidents===
* On January 23, 2010, an accidental release of phosgene gas at a DuPont facility in West Virginia killed one employee.&lt;ref&gt;https://www.csb.gov/dupont-corporation-toxic-chemical-releases/&lt;/ref&gt;

